sequenceDiagram
  autonumber

  participant U as User (Browser)
  participant SPA as Stitch Web App (SPA)
  participant API as Stitch API
  participant DB as Metadata DB (tenantId scoped)
  participant S3 as S3 (Original files)
  participant Q as SQS (Audit Queue)
  participant ORCH as Lambda (Audit Orchestrator)
  participant EX as Lambda (Extract + Locate)
  participant BR as Bedrock (LLM)
  participant OS as OpenSearch (Optional lookup)

  Note over U,SPA: User is in File Workspace and clicks Audit
  U->>SPA: Run Audit
  SPA->>API: POST /files/{fileId}/audit-runs
  API->>DB: Create auditRun (status=Queued)
  API->>Q: Enqueue (tenantId, fileId, auditRunId, s3Key)
  API-->>SPA: 202 Accepted (auditRunId)
  SPA-->>U: Show "Audit running"

  Note over Q,ORCH: Async processing
  Q-->>ORCH: SQS message
  ORCH->>DB: Update auditRun status=Running
  ORCH->>EX: Invoke (tenantId, fileId, auditRunId)

  Note over EX: Goal: produce findings with page references and highlight regions
  EX->>S3: GET file bytes
  EX->>EX: Parse PDF/Excel into pages/sheets
  EX->>EX: Extract text + tables + image-derived text
  EX->>EX: Build page map (pageNumber, text offsets, bounding boxes)
  EX->>EX: Redact PII before any LLM call (sanitized content only)

  opt Brand terminology + prior attributes
    EX->>OS: Query tenant terminology / similar styles
    OS-->>EX: Terminology + known attribute patterns
  end

  EX->>BR: Prompt: detect inconsistencies using examples
  Note over BR: Return structured JSON findings\n(each with pageNumber + anchor text)
  BR-->>EX: Findings JSON

  EX->>EX: Resolve each finding to exact highlight region<br/>(bounding boxes from page map)
  EX->>DB: Store audit report summary + findings<br/>(status=Ready)
  EX->>DB: Store highlight anchors<br/>(pageNumber, bbox, tag)

  alt Failure
    EX->>DB: status=Failed + errorCode
  end

  Note over U,SPA: UI polls or receives update
  SPA->>API: GET /audit-runs/{auditRunId}
  API->>DB: Fetch status + findings + highlights
  API-->>SPA: 200 OK
  SPA-->>U: Render report list + click-to-jump highlights in viewer

